      "name": "Orthopedic tibial tray CFD applicability domain",
      "description": "Model is applicable to Class II total knee replacement tibial tray geometries with polyethylene insert thickness between 8 mm and 14 mm, operating under physiological gait cycles (0.8–1.2 Hz), with synovial fluid viscosity in the range 1–50 mPa·s. Extrapolation beyond these bounds requires additional validation evidence."
    },
