      "rationale": "Test samples factor is scoped out at MRL 3 for this COU. The validation strategy relies on in-vitro simulator experiments using a single representative tibial tray geometry from the device family. Sample-to-sample geometric variability is addressed through the model inputs uncertainty quantification (gap tolerance ±0.05 mm) rather than multi-sample physical testing. This is consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 1 guidance for MRL 3 computational-primary validation strategies where geometric variability is captured in the uncertainty budget."
